      <div class="msgContentFrame">I agree that we need more quest outside of the leve system and main quest lines. Just little random ones or series like the Star Onion quest in FFXI. I liked the idea of the fame system, but it did get a little grindy at times. It seems rep quest in all MMOs eventually hit a grind point, WoW, LoTRO, etc. Eventually it always becomes about farming the same item or quest to get the fame/rep as soon as possible. I agree with the OP though, I love the way these systems can be used to make you feel like you are more involved with the NPCs, Cities, etc. I love the way it can change the way NPC react to you, your access to areas, your access to rewards. If they can just do simple quest, it will help a lot, but if they could introduce a, somehow, non-grindy fame/rep system, I would love it!</div>
